					<dd class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-16456">
<p>Im a 4th year mechanical engineering/ Material science engineering double major and I enjoy baking every once in a while when im craving a chocolate cheesecake or real (without quotes) homemade  brownies (you know &#8211; Baker&#8217;s semi sweet chocolate, etc).</p>
<p>I learned from my next door neighbor who is, in my opinion, a master cookie baker, that if you want soft cookies just use ALL brown sugar; just double up on brown and skip the white. It has something to do with the molasses i believe. The cookies are slightly darker for obvious reasons.</p>
